 <purpose>
	This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for elemental topology. 
	This part of ISO 10303 provides for the definition of the overall
	class of topological elements, and includes  detailed definitions of some basic topological representation items. 
	This module contains pure topology with no geometric associations.

 </purpose>

 <inscope>
	<li>the definition of the overall class of topological elements;</li>
	<li>the definition of the basic topological constructs vertex, edge and face;</li>
	<li>connected sets of basic topological elements;</li>
	<li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="foundation_representation:1_scope">Foundation representation</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1006.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     any topological element with explicitly defined geometry. 
   </li>
 </outscope>
 <normrefs>
                <normref.inc normref="ref10303-42"/>
 </normrefs>

